    "body": "## Purpose\n\nThis PR set split_k to 1 for triton_kernels:\n* It's reported that triton has worse performance than marlin for small batch size, see https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/issues/28894. This is because the computed split_k become greater than 1 for small batch size, then triton_kernels will use torch.float32 dtype, see [here](https://github.com/triton-lang/triton/blob/v3.5.1/python/triton_kernels/triton_kernels/matmul_ogs.py#L169)\n  * split_k computation: `split_k = max(n_sms // grid_size, 1)`, see [here](https://github.com/triton-lang/triton/blob/v3.5.1/python/triton_kernels/triton_kernels/matmul_ogs_details/opt_flags_details/opt_flags_nvidia.py#L45-L54)\n  * split_k become smaller when grid_size become bigger (For example, n_sms =132 for H200, if grid_size is > 66, split_k start to become 1). grid_size become bigger when m become bigger. This explains for higher batch size (m is big), split_k become 1, dtype is bf16 precision.\n  * We found split_k start to become greater than 1 when m become smaller than 32 (roughly).\n* So this PR set split_k to 1 for Hopper (sm90). Because for big batch size, split_k is already 1. For small batch size, split_k  > 1 leads to worse performance, because it will use fp32 precision as explained above, as well as split_k doesn't make sense for small matmul.\n* Blackwell (sm100) is already setting split_k to 1, because Blackwell set is_persistent to true, this will make split_k to 1, see [here](https://github.com/triton-lang/triton/blob/v3.5.1/python/triton_kernels/triton_kernels/matmul_ogs_details/opt_flags.py#L189-L190)\n* For batch size 16, e2e output token throughput improves about 38%.\n\n## Benchmarking\n\n* bs=8\n\n```\nvllm serve openai/gpt-oss-120b \\\n  --tensor-parallel-size 1 \\\n  --max-num-seqs 8 \\\n  --no-enable-prefix-caching\n```\n```\nvllm bench serve \\\n  --model openai/gpt-oss-120b \\\n  --dataset-name sharegpt \\\n  --dataset-path ShareGPT_V3_unfiltered_cleaned_split.json \\\n  --max-concurrency 8 \\\n  --num-prompts 1000 \\\n  --num-warmups 60 \\\n  --ignore-eos\n```\n\nMain:\n\n```\n============ Serving Benchmark Result ============\nSuccessful requests:                     1000      \nFailed requests:                         0         \nMaximum request concurrency:             8         \nBenchmark duration (s):                  345.98    \nTotal input tokens:                      215312    \nTotal generated tokens:                  199033    \nRequest throughput (req/s):              2.89      \nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         575.28    \nPeak output token throughput (tok/s):    630.00    \nPeak concurrent requests:                17.00     \nTotal Token throughput (tok/s):          1197.61   \n---------------Time to First Token----------------\nMean TTFT (ms):                          42.37     \nMedian TTFT (ms):                        33.98     \nP99 TTFT (ms):                           72.38     \n-----Time per Output Token (excl. 1st token)------\nMean TPOT (ms):                          13.65     \nMedian TPOT (ms):                        13.57     \nP99 TPOT (ms):                           16.06     \n---------------Inter-token Latency----------------\nMean ITL (ms):                           13.67     \nMedian ITL (ms):                         13.29     \nP99 ITL (ms):                            31.81     \n==================================================\n```\n\nPR:\n\n```\n============ Serving Benchmark Result ============\nSuccessful requests:                     1000      \nFailed requests:                         0         \nMaximum request concurrency:             8         \nBenchmark duration (s):                  249.00    \nTotal input tokens:                      215312    \nTotal generated tokens:                  199033    \nRequest throughput (req/s):              4.02      \nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         799.32    \nPeak output token throughput (tok/s):    878.00    \nPeak concurrent requests:                19.00     \nTotal Token throughput (tok/s):          1664.02   \n---------------Time to First Token----------------\nMean TTFT (ms):                          34.82     \nMedian TTFT (ms):                        29.77     \nP99 TTFT (ms):                           75.79     \n-----Time per Output Token (excl. 1st token)------\nMean TPOT (ms):                          9.80      \nMedian TPOT (ms):                        9.69      \nP99 TPOT (ms):                           12.36     \n---------------Inter-token Latency----------------\nMean ITL (ms):                           9.82      \nMedian ITL (ms):                         9.33      \nP99 ITL (ms):                            31.92     \n==================================================\n```\n\nFor small batch size, Output token throughput improves from 575.28 to 799.32 (38.9% improvement).\n\n* bs=256\n\n```\nvllm serve openai/gpt-oss-120b \\\n  --tensor-parallel-size 1 \\\n  --max-num-seqs 256 \\\n  --no-enable-prefix-caching\n```\n```\nvllm bench serve \\\n  --model openai/gpt-oss-120b \\\n  --dataset-name sharegpt \\\n  --dataset-path ShareGPT_V3_unfiltered_cleaned_split.json \\\n  --max-concurrency 256 \\\n  --num-prompts 1000 \\\n  --num-warmups 60 \\\n  --ignore-eos\n```\n\nMain:\n\n```\n============ Serving Benchmark Result ============\nSuccessful requests:                     1000      \nFailed requests:                         0         \nMaximum request concurrency:             256       \nBenchmark duration (s):                  6.12      \nTotal input tokens:                      215312    \nTotal generated tokens:                  2000      \nRequest throughput (req/s):              163.38    \nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         326.77    \nPeak output token throughput (tok/s):    514.00    \nPeak concurrent requests:                516.00    \nTotal Token throughput (tok/s):          35505.22  \n---------------Time to First Token----------------\nMean TTFT (ms):                          993.25    \nMedian TTFT (ms):                        942.59    \nP99 TTFT (ms):                           1409.40   \n-----Time per Output Token (excl. 1st token)------\nMean TPOT (ms):                          220.68    \nMedian TPOT (ms):                        187.72    \nP99 TPOT (ms):                           1118.59   \n---------------Inter-token Latency----------------\nMean ITL (ms):                           220.68    \nMedian ITL (ms):                         187.72    \nP99 ITL (ms):                            1118.59   \n==================================================\n```\n\nPR:\n\n```\n============ Serving Benchmark Result ============\nSuccessful requests:                     1000      \nFailed requests:                         0         \nMaximum request concurrency:             256       \nBenchmark duration (s):                  6.09      \nTotal input tokens:                      215312    \nTotal generated tokens:                  2000      \nRequest throughput (req/s):              164.09    \nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         328.17    \nPeak output token throughput (tok/s):    506.00    \nPeak concurrent requests:                510.00    \nTotal Token throughput (tok/s):          35657.81  \n---------------Time to First Token----------------\nMean TTFT (ms):                          999.02    \nMedian TTFT (ms):                        944.59    \nP99 TTFT (ms):                           2229.85   \n-----Time per Output Token (excl. 1st token)------\nMean TPOT (ms):                          214.58    \nMedian TPOT (ms):                        187.76    \nP99 TPOT (ms):                           1110.71   \n---------------Inter-token Latency----------------\nMean ITL (ms):                           214.58    \nMedian ITL (ms):                         187.76    \nP99 ITL (ms):                            1110.71   \n==================================================\n```\n\nFor big batch size, there's no performance regression.\n\n## Profiling\n\nMain:\n\n<img width=\"1681\" height=\"775\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-12-11 at 4 29 15 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5a331b1d-fa62-4f60-9873-a3d284761d55\" />\n\nPR:\n\n<img width=\"1681\" height=\"836\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-12-11 at 4 39 40 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/42f640cb-da86-4827-8a5a-d7618298b0bf\" />\n\nBefore the change, matmul kernels called in decode are `_matmul_ogs_NNT_fp32xbf16xmxfp4_16x256x128x5` (interpretation: `_matmul_ogs_{layouts}_{y_dtype}x{x_dtype}x{w_dtype}_{BLOCK_M}x{BLOCK_N}x{BLOCK_K}x{SPLIT_K}`), output dtype is fp32, and split_k=5.\n\nAfter the change, matmul kernels called in decode are `_matmul_ogs_NNT_bf16xbf16xmxfp4_16x256x128x1`and `_matmul_ogs_NNT_bf16xbf16xmxfp4_16x256x128x1_swiglu`, output dtype is bf16, and split_k=1.\n\n## Accuracy Testing\n\n```\nOPENAI_API_KEY=EMPTY python3 -m gpt_oss.evals --model openai/gpt-oss-120b --eval gpqa --n-threads 200 --reasoning-effort low\n```\n\n* bs=8\n\nMain:\n\n```\nWriting report to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_133922.html\n{'chars': np.float64(172.55618686868686), 'chars:std': np.float64(348.6077494902429), 'score': np.float64(0.6590909090909091), 'score:std': np.float64(0.4740148548775957)}\nWriting results to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_133922.json\nWriting all results to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_133922_allresults.json\n[{'eval_name': 'gpqa', 'model_name': 'openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_133922', 'metric': 0.6590909090909091}]\n```\n\nPR:\n\n```\nWriting report to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_151013.html\n{'chars': np.float64(166.08585858585857), 'chars:std': np.float64(350.5205007074223), 'score': np.float64(0.6521464646464646), 'score:std': np.float64(0.4762892538107302)}\nWriting results to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_151013.json\nWriting all results to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_151013_allresults.json\n[{'eval_name': 'gpqa', 'model_name': 'openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_151013', 'metric': 0.6521464646464646}]\n```\n\nFor small batch size, accuracy drops slightly most likely because precision changed from fp32 to bf16.\n\n* bs=256\n\nMain:\n\n```\nWriting report to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_164544.html\n{'chars': np.float64(174.32386363636363), 'chars:std': np.float64(349.48870198386277), 'score': np.float64(0.6502525252525253), 'score:std': np.float64(0.476890111718873)}\nWriting results to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_164544.json\nWriting all results to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_164544_allresults.json\n[{'eval_name': 'gpqa', 'model_name': 'openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_164544', 'metric': 0.6502525252525253}]\n```\n\nPR:\n\n```\nWriting report to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_171342.html\n{'chars': np.float64(176.37626262626262), 'chars:std': np.float64(346.33242896923326), 'score': np.float64(0.6590909090909091), 'score:std': np.float64(0.4740148548775957)}\nWriting results to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_171342.json\nWriting all results to /tmp/gpqa_openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_171342_allresults.json\n[{'eval_name': 'gpqa', 'model_name': 'openai__gpt-oss-120b-low_temp1.0_20251211_171342', 'metric': 0.6590909090909091}]\n```\n\nFor big batch size, there's no regression.\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
